Adjust rack to top position and heat broiler to high or #oven{} to 500 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise), then slice crosswise into ⅓-inch-thick halfmoons. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Broil or bake until golden brown and tender, ~{7-10%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Meanwhile, heat a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz} and cook, flipping occasionally, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. (If bacon starts to brown too quickly, lower heat to medium.) Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Reserve 1 TBSP bacon fat (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop bacon.

Once water is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Reserve ¼ cup pasta cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), then drain. Meanwhile, mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Heat pot used for tortelloni over medium heat. Add reserved bacon fat, garlic, and @peas{6%oz}. Cook, stirring, until garlic is fragrant and peas are warmed through, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 2 TBSP reserved pasta cooking water (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

Add zucchini, tortelloni, @sour cream{4%tbsp}, half the bacon, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pot; toss to combine. If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce. Turn off heat. Stir in a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with remaining bacon and as much lemon zest as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.